<h4>Categorical variables</h4>
<h5>One hot encoding</h5>
One hot encoding is the process of turning categorical variables in numerical values so that they can be used in mathematical formulas.
The new variables that are created are called Dummy Variables, and they only contain 1 or 0, indicating whether they are in that category or not respectively.
