<h5>The dummy variable trap</h5>
Note that assuming all of the rows of data fall into one of these categories, any of these resulting variables can be derived from the others.
{{latex-maths expr="\tag{2} England = 1 - India - Japan" display=true}}

Therefore they are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multicollinearity">Multicollinear</a>, and including all of them is going to give worse results.
To deal with this, and avoid the Dummy variable trap, we strip one of the variables off.
